short_description: The function performs cluster prediction on test data based on the cluster model generated by KMeans VALIB function and generates a dataset containing progress report with two columns, a timestamp, and a progress message. There is an additional required input table that specifies the model used by the VALIB KMeans function; additional datasets can be added in the Dataiku Input/Output tab.
long_description: The function performs cluster prediction on test data based on the cluster model generated by KMeans VALIB function and generates a dataset containing progress report with two columns, a timestamp, and a progress message. There is an additional required input table that specifies the model used by the VALIB KMeans function; additional datasets can be added in the Dataiku Input/Output tab.

argument_clauses.name: IndexColumns
argument_clauses.rDescription: Specifies the names of one or more columns in the input teradataml DataFrame to use as the primary index of the scored output DataFrame.
argument_clauses.description: Specifies the names of one or more columns in the input teradataml DataFrame to use as the primary index of the scored output DataFrame.

argument_clauses.name: ClusterColumnName
argument_clauses.rDescription: Specifies the name of the column representing cluster identifier.
argument_clauses.description: Specifies the name of the column representing cluster identifier.

argument_clauses.name: Accumulate
argument_clauses.rDescription: Specifies the names of one or more columns from the input teradataml DataFrame that can be passed along to the output teradataml DataFrame.
argument_clauses.description: Specifies the names of one or more columns from the input teradataml DataFrame that can be passed along to the output teradataml DataFrame.

argument_clauses.name: Fallback
argument_clauses.rDescription: Specifies an optional flag to indicate ('True'), that the scored output teradataml DataFrame has the fallback attribute (that is, have a mirrored copy).
argument_clauses.description: Specifies an optional flag to indicate ('True'), that the scored output teradataml DataFrame has the fallback attribute (that is, have a mirrored copy).
